msgid "The Frame"
msgstr ""

# c775d18fb8594d4eaca4dd0ad4fc36da
#: ../source/frame.rst:5
msgid ""
"The Frame is the black border around the screen that holds the View icons, "
"Activity taskbar, clipboard, wireless connections, battery level, incoming "
"invitations and notifications, buddies, and global information that is used "
"across all views."
msgstr ""

# cc6049611257498aab61b4b7cc73fcbc
#: ../source/frame.rst:8
msgid "Accessing the Frame"
msgstr ""

# 2f635541c2664aab8489ecc3fdce96cd
#: ../source/frame.rst:10
msgid "You can access the frame from any view in 2 ways:"
msgstr ""

# efe5afc275dc4bcda69eb8b87242edde
#: ../source/frame.rst:12
msgid ""
"By using the Frame Key on the keyboard. On XO laptops the Frame key is the "
"square icon on the upper right hand corner of your keyboard, on other "
"laptops you can use the F6 key."
msgstr ""

# ba5f7bfcb52a4fcab6025a876ee3357f
#: ../source/frame.rst:13
msgid ""
"By moving the cursor to the edges or corners of your screen. (There are "
"several options you can configure in this area, please refer to the My "
"Settings section for more details.)"
msgstr ""

# 2d64642eabfe4b5e9e6a346e19e58061
#: ../source/frame.rst:15
msgid ""
"In the XO-4, with touch screen, is possible show the frame sliding a finger, "
"from the top of the screen, a few centimeters. The same gesture will hide "
"the frame too."
msgstr ""

